reviews.text: I walked in for my first time tonight.  I've lived up the street for years. I see 525 Pizza all the time. Scared to try.  I'm glad I conquered my fears. The crust was perfect. Sauce great. The sauce did not over power the flavors. Crunchy bottom. Soft on top. The flavors came together very well. The owner said this would be my new pizza place. We'll he is right. Next time I will try the Funky Chicken.

We walked into this place a bit early for lunch, so we decided to try out the pizza anyway.  No regrets!  Pizza was support tasty; the crust was nice without being hard.  The garlic bread was not my favorite but my son liked it very much.
The service was good and the man making the pizza was quick and very nice to us.  This is certainly a place we will return to for a pie.  They also have a few other items on the men√∫, like hummus and the  mediterrean pizza üçï  that looked quite interesting.

We were late in picking up our pizza (got waylaid at the grocery) and they called us! They kept our delicious pizzas warm. I am a crust girl and this place has both thick and thin crust done right. The sauce was flavorful and the toppings were high quality.

The staff was so friendly and kind. Bought 3 Mama Mia sized pizzas, all stuffed crust for my daughters birthday, was only 110 for all three pizzas. They were absolutely delicious. At the parlor as a gift to my daughter, they made her a special personal garlic bread with a pepperoni and cheese flower. Very cool. Highly recommend 525 Pizza when you're in the Fresno area.
Great pizza and great people. Support local because it‚Äôs better than any of the larger chains üëç

detailedReviews.text: Being of Italian descent, I have to admit that I haven‚Äôt tasted such an authentic pizza anywhere outside of Italy until I found this hidden gem of a place called Pizza 525. The place is extremely clean, everyone is super kind and professional but above all the pizza is to die for! The crust is layered, and super tasty! The toppings are fresh and of the best quality, the cheese tastes like home made mozzarella! Wow! My family and I will only buy our pizzas from here going forward and recommend this place to everyone who is into authentic Italian style pizza made from fresh ingredients! Yummmmmmm

The cheese they used was not only unappetizing but also unevenly distributed, with a huge glob dumped right in the center of the pizza which ruined the entire pizza - it also lacked sauce. The only redeeming quality was the cheesy garlic bread. First and Last visit.
